All Implemented Interfaces:
Sender, SendSource
class ICBInputFilter
extends SendFilter

This class is a filter on incoming data from an ICB connection. It knows what sort of messages to expect, turning everything into events (speech, etc) and various calls (like setting nicknames and topics). It expects to be handed char-stream input from a ReaderSender. Any non-char[] input is just passed straight through.

Author:
Dan Bornstein, danfuzz@milk.com
